<section class="section container" id="help">

    <div class="grid">
        <div class="column-8">
            <h2>Help</h2>
            <p>
                Need help? First, please be sure to look at our list of <a href="#faq">frequently asked questions</a> below. {{#if video-link}}If you're brand new to {{title}} JS, you may also want to watch our <a href="{{video-link}}" target="_blank">introductory video</a>.{{/if}}
            </p>
            <p>
                If you don't find an answer there, try our <a href="{{zendesk-link}}">support forums</a> or use our <a href="https://knightlab.zendesk.com/anonymous_requests/new">tech support web form.</a> <strong>Please be clear</strong> with your question, <strong>include a link to your project</strong>, and if appropriate, a link to a page which shows the issue with which you need help. <strong>We can only answer support questions in English.</strong> We try to be prompt, but please understand that we do not have a dedicated tech support staff.
            </p>
            <p class="note">
                <strong>Find a bug?</strong> If you are confident you have found a bug, please report it as <a href="{{github-link}}">a GitHub issue</a>. Be sure to include detailed instructions on how to reproduce the bug. If you're not sure, please start with <a href="https://knightlab.zendesk.com/anonymous_requests/new">the tech support system</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="column-4">
            <h3>Technical documentation</h3>
            <p>Go further with {{title}}:</p>
            <ul>
                {{#each tech_docs}}
                    <li><a href="{{this.link}}">{{this.title}}</a></li>
                {{/each}}
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    {{partials 'faq' this }}

</section>
